history.content: According to the website:  "All enrolled students must be able to attend the full AM and PM blocks" so you can't just watch the webcast unfortunately. It seems like you have to be there in person.

children.subject: *must* sometimes means optional if they don't really enforce that in some sort of way (like in class quizzes). I don't know how important it is to go to classes compared to not going to classes but watching the lecture videos for cs160.

history.content:
The student above is correct. Students will need to attend all portions of the scheduled lecture during which at some parts of the semester project groups will meet supported by teaching staff.

In any event, making plans assuming the instructor is lying to you before class even starts is not the best way to approach the material.

I am taking cs160 for sure next semester. However there is another class which I am planning to take has one hour overlap with cs160 (Th 1-2pm). From the website http://teaching.paulos.net/cs160_FL2015/ the instructor says that students must enroll both blocks. Is it safe for me to go to another class and maybe watch the webcast for 160 (if there are webcasts)? There are no conflicts for final btw.

Thanks for any inputs.
